              <p align="center"><font face="Arial" size="2" color="#000080"><b>NOR
              Guild Name Policy</b></font>
              <p>&nbsp;
              <p><font face="Arial" size="2">All members of The New Outriders shall choose their own official Main Guild Name that conforms to the following rules:<br>
              <br>
              1. Each member is limited to one Main Guild Name to be listed on the Branch Roster where they play. Only the Main Guild Name will be counted towards the Branch Totals.  A member may not join any other guild with their main guild name while they are a member of NOR.<br>
              <br>
              2. Members are permitted to make additional or alternate characters/screen names that may be guild tagged. All guild tagged characters/alternates should be listed below their main name on the Branch Roster where they play.  An effort should be made to keep your alternate names similar, but this is not a requirement.  All of these characters are considered one Member/Persona and will abide by all NOR conventions.<br>
              <br>
              3. Each alternate character will obtain approval of the Duke or Duchess (or his/her designees) before being tagged.  Dukes and Duchesses may withhold approval or refuse tagging of an alternate name or character, at their discretion.<br>
              <br>
              4. Any alternate that is de-tagged as a NOR will not be permitted to be retagged.  Using NOR to level an alternate character only to remove them to another guild may be the cause of disciplinary action.<br>
              <br>
              5. De-tagging of your Main Guild Name character is considered as a resignation from NOR.<br>
              <br>
              6. Branches may, at their discretion, impose further naming conventions such as a Guild Epi or a required log-in announcement.<br>
              <br>
              7. All name changes require prior Duke or Duchess approval.  Name changes may include changing a main guild name to the name of one of the member's alternate characters.<br>
              <br>
              <br>
              <br>
              <br>
              Approved by the High Council on May 21, 2000<br>
              Revised by the High Council on June 8 2002</font></p>
